cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GT

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses an architecture for reinforcement learning agents. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with planning, acting, and learning in an online setting. Additionally, since the paper applies the architecture to games with high-dimensional state spaces like images, it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of a model to generate longer trajectories of simulated experience, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, since the paper deals with optimizing performance, it may also belong to cs.GT (Game Theory).
